This paper deals with interference coordination in heterogeneous cloud radio access networks, which involves network infrastructure, communication theory, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and optimization, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as likely categories. The paper also deals with cloud computing, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves simulations, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category.
